result.name: Oma's Kitchen

reviews.text: Just go. You won't be disappointed. Must try waffles and vanilla ice cream if you're not full by that time. Generous portions. Currywurst, very nice. Mash potatoes, yum. Honey wings, so good. Oxtail with mash, heavenly.

One of my favourite restaurants on this island. Oma’s Kitchen is a German restaurant. It has a well-conditioned indoor seating and an outdoor seating by the beach side, perfect for enjoying the night view of the Tsing Ma Bridge. My recommended dish is their roasted pork knuckle. Its skin is crisp and the meat is warm and rich. They also offer beer of different sizes. Their meals are not cheap, but I think their foods justify its price.
Fish and chips were soso, Germany bread was average, meshed potato was quite good. Overal CP rato is then very low. $200hkd for 2 in afternoon tea portion.
A comfortable place to have a cup of coffee. Food is good and the price is reasonable but the table candles are not bright enough even for eating.
Nice food and good view
